# AI Assistant Platform

## Project Documentation v0.4

Last updated: 2026-03-07

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 1. Project Vision

The AI Assistant Platform is designed as a personal AI orchestration
system that allows a user to interact with multiple AI agents through a
simple interface.

Primary interface: Telegram

The system will eventually support:

-   task orchestration
-   multi-agent workflows
-   integration with multiple LLM providers
-   automated analysis and knowledge work
-   scalable SaaS architecture

The initial version focuses on personal productivity and experimentation
with AI agents.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 2. Current System Status

The infrastructure of the system has already been deployed and is
operational.

Deployment environment:

VPS Provider: Hetzner Server OS: Ubuntu 24.04 LTS Containerization:
Docker Orchestration: Docker Compose

Running containers:

-   ai_bot (Telegram bot)
-   ai_backend (FastAPI API server)
-   ai_redis (task queue)
-   ai_postgres (database)

The system can already:

-   run a Telegram bot
-   run backend API
-   communicate between services through Docker network

Development environment:

VS Code + Remote SSH connected to the VPS.

