# 7. Environment Configuration

The system configuration is stored in a .env file.

Example:

POSTGRES_DB=ai_assistant POSTGRES_USER=ai_user
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=strongpassword

DATABASE_URL=postgresql://ai_user:strongpassword@postgres:5432/ai_assistant

REDIS_URL=redis://redis:6379/0

TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=`<token>`{=html}

OPENAI_API_KEY=`<optional>`{=html} DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=`<optional>`{=html}
KIMI_API_KEY=`<optional>`{=html}

STORAGE_INPUT_DIR=/storage/input STORAGE_OUTPUT_DIR=/storage/output

BACKEND_HOST=0.0.0.0 BACKEND_PORT=8000

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 8. Current API Endpoints

GET /health

Returns backend status.

POST /tasks

Creates a new task.

Current implementation stores tasks in memory for MVP testing.

Future version will persist tasks in PostgreSQL.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 9. Telegram Bot Capabilities

Current bot commands:

/start /health

The bot communicates with backend API to verify system status.

Next step:

Add command:

/task

Which will create tasks in the backend.

